channel.title: Latest JDK1.6 could not be detected?
channel.description:
i found where to change ip but i need to compile after i change i think but it won't work :s it's dustin's compiler from pwnscape when i try to compile it says = no version of jdk1.6 was detected :S pls help
Greetz;Eson

item.title: Latest JDK1.6 could not be detected?
item.dc:creator: @Spades Spades
item.description:
@Spades wrote:

This isn’t rocket science…

@echo off title Compiler if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Finished! pause exit

Or try this one

@echo off Title Compiler "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\javac.exe" *.java pause

item.description:
@Mercifies wrote:

Search (Ctrl+F)

Let the ###### stand for your ip address

If that doesn’t work do the same thing in the client.java folder. My server only has it work in the client.java folder.
